The parallelization unlocks the 64-core CPU that was previously idle. The threshold precomputation eliminates expensive per-row floating-point operations. These are Level 0 anti-patterns (single-threaded on multi-core CPU, unnecessary floating-point in hot loop) that can easily cause 10-100x slowdowns.